[[Reverend]] '''Chu Yiu-ming''' ({{zh|朱耀明}}, born 10 January 1944 in [[Hong Kong]]) is the minister of [[Chai Wan]] [[Baptist Church]] in Hong Kong.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} He is one of the founders of [[Occupy Central with Love and Peace|Occupy Central]] Campaign to strive for [[Universal suffrage in Hong Kong|universal suffrage]] of [[Hong Kong Chief Executive election, 2017|Hong Kong Chief Executive Election in 2017]].<ref>[http://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/article/1226665/occupy-central-seeking-support-women-workers-after-criticism Occupy Central seeking support from women, workers after criticism]</ref>

