The '''Ministry of Public Health''' ({{lang-fr|Ministère de la Santé Publique}}) is the health ministry of the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
It has a [[public health system]] based loosely on the historical [[Belgian Congo|Belgian colonial]] public health system. The ministry is largely a policy and oversight organization, with operational functions embodied within a number of subordinate ministry organizations, including the [[Institute of Tropical Medicine (Democratic Republic of the Congo)|Institute of Tropical Medicine]], [[Institute of Biomedical Research (Democratic Republic of the Congo)|Institute of Biomedical Research]] (''Institut National de Recherché Biomédicale'') and the [[Kinshasa School of Public Health]]. The latter trains physicians in public health, staffs the public health infrastructure composed of Health Zones, including the Health Zone doctors who provide both public health services and partial staffing of district hospitals.
In November 2012,{{fact|date=March 2015}} Dr. [[Félix Kabange Numbi]] was appointed Health Minister of the Democratic Republic of the Congo.<ref>"[http://www.minisanterdc.cd/new/index.php/motmin Mots du ministre]." Ministry of Public Health. Consulté le 25 mars 2015.</ref> As of 2018, the position is held by [[Oly Ilunga Kalenga]].<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.minisanterdc.cd/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=158:audiance-accordee-par-dr-oly-ilunga-kalenga-nouveau-ministre-de-la-sante-publique-a-au-dr-allarangar-yokouide-representant-de-l-oms-en-rdc&catid=9&Itemid=207 |title=Audiance accordée par Dr Oly Ilunga Kalenga, nouveau Ministre de la Santé Publique a au Dr Allarangar Yokouidé, Représentant de l’OMS en RDC |publisher=DRC Ministry of Public Health |date= |accessdate=22 May 2018}}</ref>
